      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is true that the economic evidence strongly favors the efficiency and consumer benefits of free trade. Protectionism, when implemented broadly, functions as a regressive tax that disproportionately harms lower-income consumers. The \"debate\" exists because political actors often prioritize domestic industry lobbying over pure economic theory. Therefore, while free trade is the dominant economic consensus, protectionist policies are often driven by political agendas rather than pure economic logic.",
